Here are both approaches using `IQueryAttributable` on the ViewModel.

**1. Register the route** in `AppShell.xaml.cs`:

```csharp
Routing.RegisterRoute("productdetails", typeof(ProductDetailsPage));
```

**2. Navigate from ProductListPage** (e.g., on CollectionView `SelectionChanged`):

```csharp
// Approach A — string query parameter
await Shell.Current.GoToAsync($"productdetails?productId={product.Id}");

// Approach B — pass the full object
var parameters = new ShellNavigationQueryParameters
{
    { "product", product }
};
await Shell.Current.GoToAsync("productdetails", parameters);
```

**3. Receive on the ViewModel** with `IQueryAttributable`:

```csharp
public partial class ProductDetailsViewModel : ObservableObject, IQueryAttributable
{
    [ObservableProperty]
    private string _productId;

    [ObservableProperty]
    private Product _product;

    public void ApplyQueryAttributes(IDictionary<string, object> query)
    {
        // Approach A — string ID from query string
        if (query.TryGetValue("productId", out var id))
        {
            ProductId = id.ToString();
            // Load full product from a service, etc.
        }

        // Approach B — full object via ShellNavigationQueryParameters
        if (query.TryGetValue("product", out var obj) && obj is Product p)
        {
            Product = p;
            ProductId = p.Id;
        }
    }
}
```

**4. Wire the ViewModel** on `ProductDetailsPage`:

```xml
<ContentPage xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui"
             xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml"
             xmlns:vm="clr-namespace:MyApp.ViewModels"
             x:Class="MyApp.Views.ProductDetailsPage"
             x:DataType="vm:ProductDetailsViewModel">
    <!-- BindingContext set via DI constructor injection -->
</ContentPage>
```

**Key points:**

- **Query strings** (`?productId=42`) serialize everything to strings — good for simple IDs and deep-link support.
- **`ShellNavigationQueryParameters`** passes live object references — no serialization, but only works for in-app navigation.
- Both arrive in the same `ApplyQueryAttributes` dictionary, so the ViewModel can handle either approach.
- Always `await` the `GoToAsync` call to avoid race conditions.
